			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">As dawn broke over the rocky crags of the Rathe Mountains, the Trolls stirred.  Groff, whimpering and kicking in his restless sleep disturbed what remained of the now long smoldering fire, tossing nearly dead embers into Orgak's back.  Mere moments passed before the once dying coals, fortified by Trollish fuel began once again to brightly glow. 
<br />

<br />
"ARROOOUUUGHHAAAA!" Orgak shouted as he jumped up, slapping his own back and dancing around the remains of the ruined bandit camp.
<br />

<br />
Thurgga bolted upright, sure that she was about to become decoration for the underside of a giant's foot, and looked about nervously, huddling closer in to the hillside and putting the two Trolls, one sleeping soundly and one dancing about like a madman, between her and whatever danger might be lurking in the gloomy distance.
<br />

<br />
Finally managing to extinguish the embers, Orgak roughly kicked Groff in the side before turning to Thurgga. 
<br />

<br />
"Since dumhed heer wake mez up by settin me on fiyur, gess yous best start wit da brekfust." He growled at the young Ogre, nodding to some meager provisions left from the previous night's feast.
<br />

<br />
Puzzled as to what one thing had to do with the other, Thurgga raised her eyebrows, but noting the scowl on his face, she quickly began stoking a new fire further away from the still sleeping Groff. 
<br />

<br />
Roused by the smell of cooking bandit, Groff rolled over and began scratching, sleep still hanging heavy over his head while Orgak muttered angrily, rustling around in his pack for some weeds to make a soothing salve for the singed areas on his back.
<br />

<br />
"Wut youz doin? Too erlee ta makes da noize.... &lt;sniff, sniff&gt;  Mmm... Gud gurl, gimme brekfust."
<br />

<br />
Orgak merely growled loudly as he continued to rummage, softly cursing the names of the items he found in his pack that were not soothing salve weed. 
<br />

<br />
"Cheep tin nekluss frum inkies, haff-ting hat, haff-ting toe, rusty nife, wurms, broke fishy poal, sparkly dat woofy gives me... haff a blanket...errr....."
<br />

<br />
Turning to Groff with a puzzled look on his face, he held his hand up to the light of the fire revealing a yellowish gem faceted and sparkling.
<br />

<br />
"Didunt mez trow dis away?  Stupy woofy!"
<br />

<br />
He wound up and threw the gem far into the distance, then with another curse turned back to his pack to continue his search for salve weed. A moment passed before Orgak uttered the longest, most vile string of curses Thurgga had likely ever heard in her short time on Norrath.  Spinning around to face his companions, he once again held aloft a yellowish gem.
<br />

<br />
"Didunt youz trow dat away?" Groff asked, clearly confused.
<br />

<br />
Thurgga opened her mouth as if to say something, but then thought better of it, and continued preparing the morning meal.
<br />

<br />
"ROOOAAARRR" Orgak roared.  Once again he reared back to throw the gem into the quickly fading darkness.
<br />

<br />
"Orgak no can get rid uv shiney dat way..." Thurgga mumbled.
<br />

<br />
The angry shaman stopped his windup so abruptly he almost tossed himself head first into the newly crackling fire.  He turned a suspicious look to Thurgga, then shot an equally suspicious glance at Groff, sure now that he was the butt of some elaborate joke concocted by the pair.
<br />

<br />
"Whutchoo meens, gurl?" He barked.
<br />

<br />
"Buuk sez dat shiney 'No Drop'.  Yous no gives it away or trows it away. Has ta keeps it, or crushes it."
<br />

<br />
"!@(*&$##*(@##*(!*(#$(*@#(*!@&$&%)_#$(&%*(@#(*&()!*@&($*(!*&@#(*$(%*&(@#*&(!@()$(*&(@#&(*@#^.....&lt;gasp&gt;..$&(@*#)($(*&*(!@&)()*$&)!(*@&!!!!" Orgak screamed, causing several basilisks to change their minds about an early morning sunning, and knocking several drakes straight out of the air.
<br />

<br />
Thurgga nearly dropped the scraps of meat she was preparing into the fire, her eyes going wide with fear and shock.  Groff simply nodded appreciatively and yawned, stretching.  
<br />

<br />
"Luks like yous stuk wit da woofy shiney.  Cood be wurse.  Cood be a woofy inky.  Den wez has ta share da brekfust.... Gimme heer gurl, I'ze hungrys." He said, turning to a skewer of roast bandit and slipping it out of the still startled Ogre girl's hand, commencing to tear the meat off in great hunks with his crooked, yellowed teeth.  Grumbling, Orgak nodded, conceding that it indeed could be worse and that he was also hungry.  Reaching for a skewer, he tossed the gem over his shoulder in the direction of the nearest crevice in the stone hill behind him, glancing out of the corner of his eye to see if his ploy had succeeded. 
<br />

<br />
Mid-air, the sparkling stone swerved sharply, flinging itself instead into the dark opening of Orgak's pack.  Sitting down heavily with a curse, the shaman began to swallow hunks of meat whole, all the while muttering and musing over the unsatisfactory beginning to another day.  Groff sat and chuckled as he ate.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=348308">Groff Gorespiller</a>
<br />
Troll Dread Lord
<br />
Expatriot of Grobb
<br />
<font color="maroon">Wielder of Greenmist</font>
<br />
Zebuxoruk</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
