			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The Mountains known as Rathe let the group out at the shore of the like-named lake.  As swimming took a great deal of effort, using levitation was always a preferred method for dealing with water.  
<br />

<br />
Yesterday's full bellies were now today's growling stomachs.  Orc encampments were peppered along the perimeter, but Orc was known to taste like ass.  (Which Groff had confirmed some time ago while rising to the challenge of a dare.)  
<br />

<br />
Nevertheless, Orcs could be skilled hunters, so stopping in for a bite at the nearest encampment seemed only proper.  These particular Orcs weren't as willing to stand up to the trio as the long ago digested bandits had been.  So, the camp was forfeited in their flight. Unfortunately, the camp was devoid of anything edible.  
<br />

<br />
One Orc, presumably a farmer or a criminal working off some form of community service, had abandoned his shovel in his rush to be away.  Had Orgak not "found" the shovel, it would have gone completely unnoticed.  
<br />

<br />
"OWOOOOOH!"  he howled as the handle swung up to meet his crooked nose.  Thurgga, always the helpful one, quickly grabbed the handle to remove it from Orgak's face.  Unfortunately, the blade was still under the Troll's foot and its removal placed him firmly on his back.  "AW !@#$ !#@$%#%.  STOOPID GURL!"  
<br />

<br />
Thurgga now had the shovel behind her back, trying to forget it existed.  Fear and dread filled her features.   Groff had been observing the scene with a thoughtful look on his face.  "Gurl, gif shufl back to Orgak."  She looked his way, all the blood missing from her face.  "Go on, do it."  Thurgga presented the shovel to Orgak, prepared for the iminent barrage of cursing that would come her way.  
<br />

<br />
Instead, Orgak turned to Groff "Whut youz wunt me to do wit stoopid shufl?"  
<br />

<br />
Groff simply said.  "Hit me wit it."  
<br />

<br />
In his present state, Orgak thought it sounded like a particularly good idea.  So, he snatched the shovel from the Ogre girl's hand and made his way toward Groff.  Without a word he started swinging as though he meant it.  Groff stepped away from every blow with little effort.  Winded, the Shaman finally stopped and said "If youz wunt hit, youz stand still.  Don't youz worry, I make it a good un."  
<br />

<br />
Taking on the posture of a wise teacher (which looked particularly out of place on him) Groff replied "youz need practis.  Youz keep dat shufl and uze it to kill stuff."  He pulled the subject from Orgak's grip and gave it a few deft turns.  "Gud balans, you uze it from now on."  
<br />

<br />
"I no needz practus and I no needz stoopy shufl!  Got majuk ya know."  Groff drove his shoulder into Orgak's chest, knocking him over.
<br />

<br />
"What dat for?" said Orgak.  
<br />

<br />
"Where youz majuks den?"  He asked with a ridiculous attempt to raise an eyebrow that looked more like a provocative gesture.  
<br />

<br />
Dusting himself off, Orgak rose with shovel in hand.  "Great, we gotz uzeluss woofy shiney, uzeluss stupy shufl, and now all wez need iz uzeless Ogre gurl to eatz our food."  Thurgga blushed.<br />_________________<br />65 Troll Shaman 
