			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">With a sizzling crackle of magical energy, the Trio was instantly hurled through space to land in the center of a small platform in an enormous stone cavern.  Thurgga’s eyes were wide and wild with fear, and her normally pink skin took on an abnormally greenish tint as she landed on her back side with a thump.  She looked up, eyes wide, at the volumnous cavern above her, momentarily awestruck.
<br />

<br />
”Urp, gurgle”, her stomach protested, bringing the Ogre girl back to her senses and forcing her to focus on the platform around her.  Groff and Orgak had landed on their thickly calloused feet and were quickly securing their gear amongst a sea of small pink bodies.  Thurgga scrambled to her feet under heavy protest from her churning belly, rushing to snatch up stray equipment and push her way as close to the two Trolls as possible.
<br />

<br />
”Urp, gurglegrowl, Pfffssszzzzttt!” she sounded, like a trumpet as she sidled up next to her companions.  A passing halfling, caught in the gastronomic uproar, began to cough violently, his eyes watering.
<br />

<br />
”Watch dat, gurl.  Youz Beest Lord, not singy-songy Bard.  No let out area spell like dat or youz bring guards down on us heds.” Groff chided, grinning at the girl.  Orgak barked a laugh as several other pinkies began to wobble on their feet and bump into each other in their rush to clear a circle around the three.  “Come now, wez go see ‘bout gets you place to stay an’ make mor leeky cookpots,” Groff chuckled as he began to walk toward the side tunnel leading to the Shadow Haven teleport pad.  Glancing over his shoulder at the still gurgling Ogress, he thought better of his plan and veered toward the tunnel to The Bazzar.  Orgak followed him, lost in his own thoughts and barely seeing the ground in front of him.  
<br />

<br />
Thurgga brought up the rear, eyes wide trying to take in all of the new sights and sounds around her while fighting down the urge to empty her already empty stomach down the back of Orgak’s breastplate.  As the Trio moved toward the tunnel, Thurgga offered a smile here and there to nearby travellers, but was always greated with a hasty retreat and scowl from a distance.  Apparently, the pinkies could not tell the difference between friendliness and flatulence…<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=348308">Groff Gorespiller</a>
<br />
Troll Dread Lord
<br />
