			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Sucking air and holding their sides, the Trolls were doubled over in the inner courtyard of the Plane of Knowledge.  Confident that they had eluded the Ogress, they plopped down and rested against the mishappen tree near the area where wizards and druids teleported into the plane.  Flavaa was sitting on the tree, idly fiddling with a loose strap on the hilt of her sword.  
<br />

<br />
"What was the hurry?  I wasn't done shopping yet."  She said.
<br />

<br />
"Gurl..." Groff wheezed "fire... in pants."  
<br />

<br />
The dark elf looked confused for a moment and then decided that Trolls hardly ever made sense anyway.  She had secured her hilt wrappings to her satisfaction when a bright light and a "POP!" from the portal area caught her attention.  "Neato!  Looks like a raid!"
<br />

<br />
Where there was once little more than trampled grass and drogmor leavings was now more than a score of beings of various races.  Humans, halflings, elves, dwarves and all manner of adventurers had appeared from nowhere.  They were talking hurriedly amongst themselves while a gnome dressed in robes shouted out orders.  Responding to his words, they quickly formed into small clusters and inspected their gear.  
<br />

<br />
"Wha's dis?  Prison break?"  Groff was squinting into the crowd.  Something had caught his eye.  "Dem all haf deh jailhouz tatz.  Lewd... Lod... Lose... whut dat say?"  Each one, regardless of race or profession had a tattoo which appeared to be in commmon tongue.  Groff was attempting to decypher it when Flavaa interrupted.
<br />

<br />
"Lodestar, silly goof.  And those aren't 'jailhouse tats,' that's a guild."  She giggled to herself, always pleased when she could be of assistance.  
<br />

<br />
Orgak seemed mildly dissappointed.  "Oh.  Me'z like dem jalehouz gurlz.  Dem haf fire in pantz, but cuter den Thurgga."
<br />

<br />
"Dem not so discrimna... er... describ... er... dem desprat too."  Groff added with a nod and a sly grin.
<br />

<br />
"Heads up Trolls!"  Came a shout from behind.  Flavaa deftly lept out of the way and the Trolls had just enough time to duck when a Barbarian in chainmail just cleared their heads as he jumped over them and the tree.  The spear he was carrying was brilliantly illuminated in the colors of the rainbow.  The lights encircling the finely crafted tip pulsed of their own accord.  Orgak caught a glimpse as the Barb careened overhead.  
<br />

<br />
"BLIND!  ME'Z BLIND!!!"  Orgak had his fist in his eyes, grinding them furiously.  The Shaman's sight was returning slowly as he squinted at his surroundings.  "Meh hatez dem stupy shiney stickers.  Why ennyone wunt ta carry dat?  It uglee and luk like big tootpik." 
<br />

<br />
"Um... Orgak..."  Flavaa began to say something and then thought better of it. 
<br />

<br />
By the time the excitement from Orgak's outburst had settled, the gathering at the portal had dissappeared.  With their wind back and nothing of interest nearby, the trio settled on preparing for departure.  They were making their way to the stone statue that would transport them to Toxxulia Forrest and ultimately Gunthak, when a cheer from what must have been scores of voices arose from behind them.  
<br />

<br />
"GOING!  GOING! GOOOONE!  AND IT'S GOOOOD!"   One voice rose over all the rest.  Groff turned to find the source of the commotion and noticed something falling from the sky just in time to catch it.  It was a gnome.  It looked up from Groff's arms with a grimace.
<br />

<br />
"Oh! Oh! It our lukky day!"  Orgak was animated and rummaging through his backpacks, presumably for cooking utensils.  The gnome's demeanor changed from one of distaste to fear.  
<br />

<br />
Flavaa interrupted the Troll's celebration. "No no boys.  He's been through enough already."  She patted their would-be lunch on the head and took on a look of sympathy.  
<br />

<br />
Groff turned his attention from the gnome in his arms to consider Flavaa dubiously.  "Lunch no fall from sky all deh time, inky.  We'z hungree."  Orgak nodded vigorously, as he finished tying on an apron.  
<br />

<br />
The gnome wiggled free of Groff's embrace and found his own feet.  "Thank you kind... dark elf." He coughed. "Your benevolence will not be forgotten.  I am Xabiktik."  He said with an awkward bow as he was a bit worse for wear from his impact with Groff's platemail.  "Great enchanter of Ak'Anon.  Now, if you'll excuse me..."  He started to back away.
<br />

<br />
He stumbled forward after backing into a wall unexpectedly.  Flavaa closed in on him with a look of concern.  "Who punted you sir Gnome?  We shall avenge you!  Yesh!"  She looked over her shoulder at Orgak with the gleam of excitement in her eyes.  Orgak bared his teeth and inhaled deeply.
<br />

<br />
"No. No.  No need for that."  He stammered hurriedly.  "I allowed them to... er... punt me.  As you so eloquently put it.  You see, I need to raise money."  
<br />

<br />
"So youz let dem kick you over deh walls."  Groff said with a snicker.  "Meh thot youz waz great mind messer-upper."  
<br />

<br />
The gnome gave a resigned shrug.  "I don't have KEI yet.  A Gnome's gotta eat."  And with that he scampered away, favoring an ankle.
<br />

<br />
A tug on Orgak's tunic drew his attention from the departing picnic.  He turned to see a human holding a candle and a rusty sword.  "Sowplzthx."  
<br />

<br />
Orgak sighed.<br />_________________<br />65 Troll Shaman 
