			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Orgak began chanting in a deep mumbling voice, waving his arms as he called upon the spirits to imbue the human with the spirit of wolf.  As the magicks settled upon the young warrior, he turned quickly and sprinted off without a word, kicking up dust clouds.
<br />

<br />
”Youz welcum, pinky!” Orgak called after the retreating human, his face wrinkling into a snarl.  “Stupy littul pinkiez, no grata..errr…gartee..errr… no thankee fer da wuffy feetz!”
<br />

<br />
He turned back to his companions, intent on continuing their journey to the riches and shineys to be found on Broken Skull island, but no sooner had he turned than he felt another tug at his sleeve.  He turned to see a human holding a candle and a rusty short sword. 
<br />

<br />
”Ah, yous come back, say thankee fer buffs, huh?” Orgak grinned.  The human looked a little confused for a moment, then spoke. “sow/sta/focus plz!”  
<br />

<br />
Orgak grunted in confusion.  “Buh..err.. Mez jus give yous wuffy feetz, wha..” he started to question the human, but was interupted by another tug on his sleeve.  Reflexively, he turned to see yet another youngling, this time a dark elf with a cracked wooden staff. “Sowplzthnkzkk~!!11!!”
<br />

<br />
Yet another tug caused Orgak to whirl around again, this time to face a high elf in gauzy blue. “can i  get a sow frm u plz thx for CR!” the elf spouted all in a rush.  Orgak looked up in horror and confusion as a steady stream of barely clad younglings began to stream toward him, their hands outstreached, all of them yammering ceaslessly for buffs.
<br />

<br />
”ARRGGHHH!” he screamed, yet the masses were unabated. “Wez gotta get out uv here!” he shouted over the din to Groff and Flavaa, then nodded toward the low rent district of the Plane of Knowledge where the evil races resided.  Mumbling quickly and waiving his arms, he imbued his companions and himself with the Spirit of a Long Suffering Bar Owner (which made their feet run fast and true, but only in retreat from the demands of work and silly people) and the three bowled through the crowd toward the stone which would take them to Paineel, city of the evil Erudites and gateway to the Stonebrunt Mountains, where a charter boat would take them on to Broken Skull Island.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=348308">Groff Gorespiller</a>
<br />
Troll Dread Lord
<br />
Expatriot of Grobb
<br />
<font color="maroon">Wielder of Greenmist</font>
