			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">After a few weeks spent finding their way through the labyrinth of tunnels knowns as the Warrens -- Flavaa constantly reminding them that a port would have sped the trip considerably -- our band of "heroes" arrive in Stonebrunt mountains.  
<br />

<br />
"Orgak, I've been meaning to ask you," Flavaa said cautiously. "Why do you wear that old beat up helmet?  It's so scarred and plain.  Why, I have a leather cap that would suit you better. "  
<br />

<br />
Orgak trudged ahead, his cheeks a darker green than the rest of his face.  He winced as Groff snickered and began to speak.  "heh, him warez deh helmut 'cuz his mudder sed he haz to.  She say him hit his hed too much."  
<br />

<br />
As Flavaa began to inquire further about this, her attention was drawn to a boat at the end of a pier that became visible as they crested the last rise. (Orgak was relieved at the change of subject.)  "OOoooooOOh!  Look at THAT!  Garsh!  That must be it!  We're there!"  She was skipping along now at a faster rate, sword bouncing against her thigh and armor clanging as she loped along.  
<br />

<br />
It was a boat indeed; well-crafted but not as large as the bloated belly -- though it was in one piece. As they grew nearer, some catlike creatures on two legs became visible -- presumably Kerran or close relatives.  
<br />

<br />
Groff stopped and removed his headgear with a wide cunning grin.  He licked a palm and slicked back the few straggling hairs on his head.  "If youz eksuze meh, dis might take all night." 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">&lt;Editor's note:  I cannot rightfully include the full details of the following encounter between Groff and the Kejekans at the dock.  This IS a rated PG forum.  Just know that afterward, it took both Orgak and Flavaa to remove the fishing pole from Groff's hindquarters.  To this day, we don't know for sure it was a Kejekan that put it there anyway.&gt;</span><br />_________________<br />65 Troll Shaman 
