				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Groff hobbled testily down the ramp, his brow wrinkled in pain and anger.  He shot several glances over his shoulder to Orgak and Flavaa as they followed him down, giggling.  “Yous too not needs be so ruff!  Now yous make Groff woks funny…  Ooooh! Dat smarts!”  A passing gnome deckhand looked up curiously at the waddling Troll, cracking a grin as he noticed the broken remains of a fishing pole strewn about the deck of the docked ship.  Orgak and Flavaa erupted into laughter, walking quickly around their limping companion.
<br />

<br />
”How wuz I to nose dat kitty wuz a cat?” Groff growled, angrily.  “Him look’d like kitty, smell’d purty two, like da fishies,” he murmered quietly to himself as he waddled up the ramp to the rock upon which a great lighthouse stood, his chafed backside stuck out at an odd angle.  With his gait impeded by his injury, his head thrust down toward the ground at each step, and so he failed to notice when Orgak stopped suddenly in front of him.
<br />

<br />
“Oof!  Hey, dat not funny, yous nose dat Groff no can see wayre he goez!” He protested, but the awestruck Shaman paid him no heed, instead staring into a large enclosed pen next to the lighthouse with his mouth agape.  Groff slowly, gingerly straightened his back, wincing several times at the tenderness in his nethers, until he could see what had stopped his friend.  Following Orgak’s gaze, it was only moments before they both stood with dumbstruck looks on their faces, eyes wide, staring at a small “herd” of strange creatures contained within the pen.
<br />

<br />
”Oooh,” Orgak exclaimed. “Purty leezurd horsiez! Me wunts wun!”
<br />

<br />
Groff looked uncertainly at the large claws that studded the beasts’ leathery scaled feet.  “Dunno, Orgak, dem luks meen… Tink wez has bettur luk wit da kitties…”<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=348308">Groff Gorespiller</a>
<br />
