			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">As the Trio landed upon the rocky, broken beach, Orgak called for a halt. “Stupy hidey invisibully spell gunna go ‘way.  Mez hate dis ting. Alwus go ‘way wen der munsters.  Den munsters bites Orgak in da arse!”
<br />

<br />
”While it’s a fine arse for a Troll, Orgak, I very much doubt that anything would want to bite into that end of you.” Flavaa murmered with a chuckle, pinching her nose playfully.
<br />

<br />
Orgak glanced up at the nearest of several broken and battered ship wrecks, following Groff’s gaze.
<br />

<br />
”Dere no luk like der any treshure in dese botes, Orgak.  Yous make Groff walk all da way here fer nuthin, Groff gunna bash yous gud,” the Shadow Knight growled.
<br />

<br />
”Pfft!  Uv corse dere no treshure in dese botes.  Dese da wuns dey use fer huntin, stupie! Luk, de aminals goes in der, den…err.. den dey catches em, eets em.  See, watch dat…errr… bug tingie.”   Orgak pointed toward a Niflik which was clicking and crawling its way across the beach attempting to cach some sort of sand flea for it’s own meal.  The flea bounced from the wet sand up onto the mouldering wooden planks of a wrecked hull and cawled deeper into the shadows.  As the trio watched, the Niflik clambored up onto the planks iteself and followed the flea inside.  Waiting expectantly for something to happen, Groff’s gaze was glued on the gaping, shadowed hole in the ship hull.  After a few moments, nothing stirred, and Groff became impatient.  
<br />

<br />
”Whut happun’d two da buggie tingie?  Groff hungry, mebbe mez go chek.  Cood has a snak on da way ta da treshur!”  He began to move forward from the concealing shadows of their rocky cliff shelter, eyes intent on the wreck, when Flavaa placed a small blue hand on his arm.
<br />

<br />
”Hold your horses there, Groffy!  You don’t know what’s in there, and you don’t know what’s around here.  Maybe Orgak’s right and the inhabitants of this island are going to come looking for their prey.”
<br />

<br />
Groff threw the Dark Elf an exasperated glare. “If mez had da horsies, no wood needs ta eets buggie tingies!  No has horsie, gunna eets bug.” He turned back toward the shipwreck just in time to see the now satisfied Niflik begin to hesitantly crawl out into the waning daylight.  Groff grinned, thinking that the creature, with it’s belly full, would now be easy prey.  Without warning, a loud crack sounded from within the hull of the wreck and before Groff or his companions could move, the entire thing came crashing down, splattering the small blue bug across the beach.  Hearing a shout from a nearby camp, Orgak’s instinct for survival got the better of him and he began to chant, waving his hands and cloaking each of the trio in a dense fog of invisibility.  Flavaa grabbed hold of Groff’s arm again, nearly dragging him off his feet up the beach and toward a rock canyon which led off of the small alcove, her charge grumbling softly about his missed opportunity to taste the “yummy pink goo” the former Niflik had contained.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=348308">Groff Gorespiller</a>
