			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The cave they had entered was apparently a passageway to something else.  The ground was uneven, jagged rocks reaching up from the ground almost as if to trip up any unmindful passersby, and littered with malignant life.  Here and there was a drogmor, sickly and foaming at the mouth with a look of madness in their eyes.  These weren't the inane seemingly-oblivious creatures like Orgak's latest charge, these were apparently infected with something horrible.  The party felt it was best to pass through the tunnel under the protection of invisibility.  
<br />

<br />
The tunnel was well-traveled, but apparently unattended.  The ground rolled in waves of treacherous terrain.  Their passing had started to feel like a journey with no end in sight.  Each turn revealed yet another long stretch of unpleasant footing and frighteningly malevolent indeginous life.  Flowers that looked, for lack of better words, hungry.  Trolls with a menacing gleam in their eyes and of course the crazed drogmors.  
<br />

<br />
To pass the time, Orgak began to sing a song from his childhood.  It was one Stragak would sing while teaching the young Trolling how to hunt elderly humans.  
<br />

<br />
"Ofur dis rivah and tru dis woodz, toz grandmudda houz we'z goooo..."  
<br />

<br />
Of course, this was all he knew of the song and so he repeated it over and over again.  Flavaa singing along in a "if you can't beat them join them" resolvement.  After a few dozen repitions, it began to wear on Groff's always-tender nerves.
<br />

<br />
Orgak began again "Ofur dis rivah.."
<br />

<br />
"Dere is NO RIVAH here..."  Groff corrected
<br />

<br />
Undaunted, the cheerful Shaman contineud "And tru diz woodz..."
<br />

<br />
"Dere is NO WOODZ here neder you nincompooper"  Groff interjected again
<br />

<br />
"Toz grandmudda houz we'z goooo...."  This time he was a bit less resolved in his recital of the verse... 
<br />

<br />
"YOU'Z GRANDMUDDA DED FRUM DA ROT LONG TIME GO, SO SHUDDUP!!"  Groff had reached the end of his already scarce patience.
<br />

<br />
Flavaa, seizing the opportunity to put an end to the recital chimed in "He does have a point, Orgak.  It doesn't really apply to this particular situation."
<br />

<br />
Orgak sighed.  Now outnumbered, he had little choice.  His brow scrunched in on itself as he thought, nodding to himself.  Finally, he started to sing once again. 
<br />

<br />
"Over deh rocks and tru deh dirt to steal shineyz from deh privatez we'z goooo..."
<br />

<br />
Flavaa giggled and looked at Groff wrily.  "Our blades know the way to slaughter and slay any mean ol' foooooOOOOE!"
<br />

<br />
Groff cast a look at the ground and mumbled something barely audible "We'z gunna beh privatez 'n' burn teh seas for deh gloree of dear ol' Grooooobb.  Orgak's butt stinkz, Flavaa'z eh twiiiink, and really a guy named BaaaaaaAAAAAwwwb!"
<br />

<br />
The trio laughed their way to the end of the passage which left them facing an small outpost belonging to the pirates of Gunthak.<br />_________________<br />65 Troll Shaman 
<br />
LFHC (Looking for Home City)
<br />
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=602910>Who says you can't wear split paw armor in your 60's?</a>
<br />

